\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 I suppose I was probably about two and a half, and ironically, then we took a train from Liverpool to Bristol, and my mother\rquote 
s parents \endash  well, my grandfather had died during the War, not of war problems - but the first memory I do have is the train pulling up at Bristol station, and my grandmother holding out a teddy bear, and I\rquote ve got that 
teddy bear upstairs. My family, my mother\rquote s family were upper bourgeoisie. But in those days, you didn\rquote t own houses, you rented, and they had a lovely house in Martock, next to the church where my mother had married \endash  there\rquote 
s a photograph there. I just remember being in this wonderful place, and hearing the bells of the church, and having that teddy. So those are my earliest memories. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
