\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Yes. You know, we couldn\rquote t put our arms on the table. You could never eat with 
your fork, shovelling peas up like that. Of course, when I went to France, you put your hands on the table like that. Everything \endash  I\rquote ve got all that in the article \endash  is bodily control. That\rquote 
s why one of the most inspiring books I read later was, Discipline
 and Punish by Foucault. So it was bodily control. I knew this inner resentment. Every book you had that was your own, it had to be passed by the Headmistress. She would look at it, and put a signature, in pencil, to see if it was all right. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
