\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, this French woman did encourage me. Then there was one who Mimi remembers, and she\rquote s written a whole poem about him, he
\rquote s called Aubrey de Selincourt and his daughter married Christopher Robin \endash  he was friendly with A.A. Milne \endash  whole sort of elite. He was retired. He\rquote 
d translated The Iliad and key Penguin texts were translated by him. He was a retired intellectual. He was inspiring, but I think he was wary of me. I mean, I didn\rquote t idolise him, but after I did get my \lquote A\rquote 
 Level in English Literature and English Language. I wrote him a really emotional letter, \'93What an inspiration you\rquote ve been\'94
, and he never replied. Whereas Mimi said she wrote him a letter and he did reply. So I think, again, did he think I was looking for a paedophile? I don\rquote t know. But 
his lectures, his teaching on Keats and Shelley - but then, at the same time, there was a thing in me that thought \endash  I didn\rquote t have the words \endash  but he represented the status quo. I think he thought, \'93
Girls are just going to be nice wives\'94. That he was passi
ng time with these girls, but there was no question of any of us going to university, it was just a pleasure and a fun for him. We were just being geared to make nice dinner conversation as the correct sort of wives. So, no, no, the only inspiration - no,
 I think it was only when I got to Oxford, but in most cases, St. Hilda\rquote s hated me as well. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, we\rquote ll come to that in a while. And you describe the School as a preparation for dependence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
\ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
