g to be a memoriam in his honour, we were all on the Left, and we would have the most amazing discussions. We were reading Marcuse. We were reading all these books that weren\rquote 
t on the syllabus. So, anyway, I graduated with a Third Class Degree. I was viva\rquote d for a 2:1, because in those days, there was no 2:1, 2:2, it was 1, 2, 3 or 4. And I arrived late for my best paper. I\rquote m giving you the background, it\rquote 
s obviously rambling but tell me if it\rquote s off the point. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
