\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, I was easing [it for him], as John Blacking \endash  who was Professor of Anthropology at Belfast, he\rquote s since died 
\endash  I told him about it, and he said, \'93You eased it, because the bachelor from Britain is, they\rquote re dodgy! There are plenty of bachelors in rural Ireland, but who is this stranger? Whereas if you come with a wife, you\rquote 
re a normal couple\'94. And he said, Blacking said, \'93You eased the way for him\'94. He was human. And also, of course, I would report to Hugh any women\rquote s conversations. Sometimes there were young women that were mesmerised that I\rquote 
d lived in London, Swinging London, you know! They thought, \'93Oh, God! Let\rquote s hear about it!\'94 I wore a mini skirt. So they would invite me to tea, and then I would come back to Hugh an
d tell him some of the things I witnessed. I worked behind the bar, I helped bring in the turf on my back. Hugh had a brilliant way, but I learnt about fieldwork. I also was shocked that he thanked everybody, you know, \'93
Thank you, Alison Sorkiss for helping me with the index\'94. Thanks somebody for pointing out this literature. It was all written in the first person! Then there was a review in the International Socialist Review or whatever, and it said, I\rquote 
ve said there that, to them, this was extraordinary th
at somebody should be living in rural Ireland. I remember when I met up with Robin Blackburn, who I used to know, when Hugh and I moved to a cottage in Upper Heyford, I bumped into Robin, because I knew him through Gareth, and he said, \'93
What are you doing living out in the country?\'94 You know, \'93What are you doing for the working class?\'94 When Hugh\rquote 
s book came out in 1973/4, it was considered amazing that a Lefty should go and live with peasants in the outer boom docks! And in the review it said how brilliant it was using an autobiographical style. It was all bullshit! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 
