\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, again, I\rquote 
ve written in an article in honour of Shirley Ardener, it was a whole festchrift - it was Shirley who came up to me, she always had these brilliant ideas! She first told me to write, and asked me to give a paper on gypsy women, and I\rquote 
d never thought of it. I thought, \'93Well, I\rquote m a Feminist\'94, I thought it was Feminist just to go to university, and I hadn\rquote t problematised women. I wrote that 
article. And there was this wonderful supportive seminar. And then, out of the blue, she said, \'93Why don\rquote t you give us a paper on your boarding school, because you\rquote re always talking about it\'94. I didn\rquote 
t even know I was always talking about it, probably because I thought every single step I had was a triumph, that I had gone to university - and she asked me to write the article. It had not occurred to me! I started writing it in \rquote 
78, I think it was - no, I remember I gave the first presentation, it was absolutely bizarre, the day before my viva for my Ph.D., so it was \lquote 77/\rquote 78, the viva was January \rquote 
78, and I remember, I gave this in Queen Elizabeth House, and there was honestly, about 60 people \endash  it was a well attended seminar in those days! And there were women in the audience, crying, came up to me, and they said, \'93You\rquote 
ve brought it all back for us\'94. You know, \'93You\rquote ve \'85 we had to fight to go to university\'94. But there were several people came up to me and said, \'93My God, what a performance!\'94 So it was thanks to 
Shirley. But, in preparing to write it, I sat in my study \endash  I had a house in Islington then, with my partner, Jim \endash  and I went through terrible depressions, just days of fighting back despair, just bringing back those memories. It wasn
\rquote t a fun thing to do, but I felt propelled to do it. But before that, I had thought I\rquote d buried it, but obviously Shirley said I was talking about it so much that she asked me to write, to do a presentation, you know. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
