\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Yes! But by this time, I\rquote d decided to changed to PPE. Because \endash  this is going back to your question \endash 
 I was absolutely sh
ocked at the teaching of French. All the literary commentaries were written by English people. I had learnt to write essays in French. You wrote all your essays in English here, and also people were proud to speak French with an English accent! And then y
ou read something on Sartre that said, \'93He doesn\rquote t look at the empirical something,\'94
 and again, it was back to, for Prelims. you just read half of Baudelaire and one Balzac novel. It was back to all this limited stuff, compared to the panoramic view. And, o
f course, I was very political, because in France I became a Socialist and an atheist. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
