Well, no, not as an Englishwoman, no. But we were there actually during the great putsch when the White French tried to overthrow de Gaulle and take everything. And I was reading Le Canard enchaine, which was the radical paper, and it was long before 
\rquote 68 or anything like that, but there were demonstrations for the Freedom of Algeria. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
