\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 No. When did I start reading Marx? I think when I was an undergrad. But I was reading de Beauvoir, that was the great book \endash 
 The Second Sex \endash  which was not on the syllabus or anything, I just discovered it. But I think that the people I mixed with were, but there was no place for a foreigner to be an activist. I mean, you hardly met French people because that\rquote 
s how Parisians survive, they switched off from foreigners. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
