\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 I think so, yes. I mean, I\rquote ve got Karl Marx\rquote s Kapital there, and Marcuse. I don\rquote 
t remember the great moment, but I joined up to the Labour Club and I was already sympathetic with CND. I went to CND meetings in my first term, and so I mixed with a whole group \endash  that\rquote 
s how I got to know Bob Rowthorne and then later Gareth Stedman-Jones. I think I got it into my head even before I went to Oxford, I said, \'93I\rquote m going to get women into the Union\'94
, because women were not allowed to be members of the Oxford Union. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Yes. Tell me the story about that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Funnily enough, because I\rquote m on the Gender Centre, you know, sometimes Union people say, \'93We want a Feminist\'94
, and about three years ago I went to speak, and the President hadn\rquote t a clue. They don\rquote t know about Feminism now, the younger males, and I sat there \endash  it was a sort of panel \endash 
 and there were all these Freshers, because it was the first/second week of term, and they wanted to come to this famous place, and I said, \'93
Do you know, when I came, we women had to be up in the balcony, like in a mosque or a synagogue, looking down at our male undergraduate contemporaries debating. We had to look down at them\'94
. I befriended a very very clever guy called Roderick Floud, who\rquote s now Sir Roderick Floud, who became professor and all that, and he was a very very good organiser, and we formed a c
ommittee, and there was Roderick, there was me, later Michael Beloff joined the bandwagon, later Jonathan Aitken, so we had Liberal, Tory, Labour, all on a committee. I\rquote 
ve since been told by students at the Union, that you can no longer lobby, but what Roderick did, because his father was to be an MP, he said, \'93You go round to all the Colleges, lobbying, finding out the members, male members, \lquote 
Are you in favour of women joining the Union?\rquote  and if they are, then you put a tick, and then on the day\'94 - And then we proposed it, not \'93we\'94
, but others, and then there was a vote, and we lobbied for 24 hours before, and it was my duty, like others, to go round all the Colleges, like with the Labour Party, \'93You said you would vote. Have you voted yet?\'94 We lost it the 
first time, and we joked, because John Sparrow, who was Head of All Souls, there was a huge letter in The Times saying, \'93All life members, please come, wherever you are, and vote against accepting women in the Union\'94
. So there was a huge group of people, they all came in coaches or something, and they probably died on the way back! So Roderick was so clever, he said, \'93Let\rquote s have a vote the next term, very quickly\'94, and we said, \'93
Half these octogenarians had died on their way home\'94, and we won the vote the next time. And Roderick was an ace. As the vote was announced, he said, \'93Judith, go out to the corridor, there\rquote 
s a list up there where you put down your name, wanting to be a member\'94. He knew the strategy, and I put my name there, and I got world publicity! I mean, people even wrote to me from Australia, saying, you know, \'93
You must be our relative because you spell your name\'94 - O K E L Y. It was announced, I\rquote ve got photo cuttings of me, you know, front page of the Daily Express, \'93The first woman member of the Oxford Union\'94. But it was symbolic. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Did you speak immediately? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
