\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
Well, I had a mad social life, you know, because there was one woman for every nine men, and I just had a wild life. But I thought I met 
the love of my life, my first term, and ironically I went back to the very building where I first met him at a CND meeting, and he walked out and pursued me. Then he organised a CND march, and the police were very clever with their loud hailers in St. Gil
es, said, \'93Could we speak to the organisers of this march?\'94
 We were going to march to Brize Norton or something, and these people came, including this guy, and a very devout Quaker who was in his fifties, and the police promptly arrested them, and they were
 accused of organising an illegal demonstration. And then he went to prison... So I really picked this guy. He dumped me after ten days, having asked me to marry him. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Did you find anyone better after that, then? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, then the idea of unique love just was total rubbish, it was bullshit. You think you\rquote 
re going to have a life partner who actually says, \'93I\rquote m madly in love with you\'94, and we wrote letters to each other when he was in prison, I visited him every week in prison, and to have, then, somebody say, \'93Don\rquote t come near me\'94
, and, \'93Don\rquote t touch me\'94, and \'93I don\rquote t want to have anything more to do with you.\'94 I went, as a day patient, to the Warneford, and I was on antidepressants and everything. So then, what was the point? So I just had casual
 relationships with anybody I liked. Then I met up with Gareth, and that was probably one of the best relationships I\rquote 
ve had, because there was no real jealousy or envy or anger, that was a lovely set up, and then we drifted apart. And then I met up with H
ugh. But I had many many lovers. And I was raped by a famous radical. Yep! Well, you know, I could just say a few - I see him on telly now. I won\rquote t say who it is, but I just think of that guy, and he parades as a radical now, and I think, \'93
You raped me! How dare you go and defend the guy with Wikkileaks. You see him on television. I think, \'93No wonder you\rquote re defending him because you know what it\rquote s like to rape\'94. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
\par 
\par Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 But on the whole it sounds like a rather positive time of life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
