\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Oh yeah, yes. Of course, I didn\rquote 
t work with my nose to the - I had been in a segregated school where you never met any men, and I had met some absolutely wonderful people who I\rquote m absolutely - it was really good. If I\rquote d just sat down and read PPE and followed Miss Crowe,
 I would - and I went to a Reunion ten years ago at St. Hilda\rquote s, and a lot of the women said, \'93God, Judith, you were an inspiration.\'94 Because at St. Hilda\rquote s, you had to sign a contract to say you wouldn\rquote 
t marry, and that was when abortion was illegal, birth control for unmarried people was illegal. There\rquote s a Reunion picture. I refused to join the school photo of first years because I thought, \'93This is just like boarding school\'94
, but I was sent it the other week from St. Hilda\rquote s because they desperately want money, and there\rquote 
s going to be another Reunion. And there, very poignantly, is one girl, she was found in bed with her boyfriend during visiting hours, and she was expelled. And Miss Major, the Principal, wrote to every university she applied to, and to h
er grant authority, saying she was unfit for education. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
