. My mother, funny enough, had been going to evening class at Garnett College, and I\rquote 
d met somebody who was a friend of a friend from Oxford, I was staying in Stevenage, and this was the great Left-wing thing to do was teach Liberal Studies in Colleges of Further Education. I didn\rquote t realise it was a whole Lefty pattern \endash 
 you taught the working class. And apprentices had a one-day release, and they\rquote d have to do engineering or something, but they had one or two hours of Liberal Studies, and I attended one of these guys classes at Stevenage,
 and that inspired me, so I registered at Garnett \endash  because, then, you could get a full grant, again. I couldn\rquote t get a grant to do an MA at the LSE, but I could get a full grant to go to Garnett. And then I flew to Belfast \endash 
 those were the days, standby, \'a325 return, from Heathrow \endash  and I would spend the weekend in Queen\rquote s, Belfast.... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
