\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Yes. I moved to Cambridge because I\rquote 
d been registered for that course, because I thought Jim was going to be there, and he said, \'93No, I\rquote m staying in Oxford\'94. And I was too late to apply., I rang up Oxford. I rang up Godfrey [Leinhart] as it happened, on the phone, and said, 
\'93Is it too late to apply?\'94 And he said, \'93What class of degree did you get?\'94 And I said, \'93A Third\'94. He said, \'93We only take serious people here\'94
, and put the phone down. But I was interviewed at Cambridge, by Meyer Fortes. I had to show, with my bank account, and because I\rquote d got this bad degree, they couldn\rquote 
t give me the one Studentship that they had, and they gave it to a total hippy who was utterly not interested, but he got the award. Anyway, I said Leach was my inspiration. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
