\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 I know! Exactly! And then in January this year, I think it was, there was a special event to open Archival Centre, because they
\rquote ve got some famous novelists \endash  A.S. Byatt, and goodness knows what \endash  and there was going to be the launch of this Archive, and I e-mailed people, and I said I would like to give my field notes to the Archive \endash  hand
written field notes of my gypsy work \endash  and they were very sweet and lovely, but they didn\rquote t - I just said I would be coming, and that you\rquote 
re supposed to e-mail somebody, and then they found out that there were so many people that I hadn\rquote t been registered, and so I didn\rquote t go to the event. But the archivist says, \'93Thank you for your great generous gift, and we\rquote 
ll be looking forward to seeing it\'94, so I will, at some point. And I said to these people on the phone, I said, \'93I am going to celebrate Newnham because it was thanks to the Cambridge Anthropology that I owe everything to Leach and Tambiah\'94. So I
\rquote ve now decided I will never give another bean to St. Hilda\rquote s, for other reasons I won\rquote t go into. But I thought I would do it to celebrate. And of course, you know, I should be grateful, and I feel ashamed that I didn\rquote 
t fully credit Esther Goody, the first or second wife of Jack Goody. Second, yes. Because he\rquote s on to a third. I had a most hopeless tutor for the first term at Newnham \endash  because you had the right for tutors, I won\rquote t say who he is 
\endash  and in the end I went to Esther Goody and I said, \'93Please could I have you as my tutor?\'94 And then I told her about doing work in the West of Ireland, and then she asked me if I\rquote d read that famous book, you mentioned it. }{
