ose two weeks, you see, I had to take on the role of the Warden and collect the rent, and that\rquote s when I found it really problematic. Because then I was immediately identified as an official, and, of course, they played it! They said, \'93We\rquote 
ve paid two months in advance\'94, and \'93Norman knows that\'94. And was I there to defend the Council? I wasn\rquote t even an employee! But that was when Don said to me, \'93You don\rquote t need to collect the rent. You don\rquote 
