Then I moved, then I was allowed to stay on all these different sites, but the problem started with Barbara. After about two or three weeks, I
 think it was before I moved on to that second site, and when I was in the B&B up the road, she summoned me back to the office, and she said, \'93Right. Now, will you compose a questionnaire?\'94 And then she kind of sighed and said, \'93
Oh, of course, you\rquote re totally inexperienced. You wouldn\rquote t even know how to begin to compose a questionnaire\'94. And I knew, from what I\rquote d said last visit, that having conducted questionnaires round Cowley, how even when you\rquote 
re finding out about shopping habits, how inept they are. And my heart sank! I said I didn\rquote t know what to do. And then she sat down, and she composed, honestly, about 15-20 pages \endash 
 you know, date of birth, experience of housing - and I used this particular question, by the way, it was not in that one, but it was in her Census, the Census question, \'93Why do you travel?\'94 Do you ask nomads, \'93Why do you travel?\'94
 My answer, when I give lectures is, \'93Judith\'94, the gypsy children would say, \'93Judith, what\rquote s it like living in a house?\'94 How can I answer? I said, \'93It\rquote s got a ceiling, it\rquote s got walls, it\rquote s got electricity, it
\rquote s got a floor\'94. How can I tell? So how can you ask nomads, \'93Why do you travel?\'94 You might be saying, \'93Why do I live in a house?\'94 So, you know, anyway, this 25 page questionnaire - and I was already established 
rapport with some of these people. I wrote a paper, which I\rquote ve never published, about the importance of people who come to you at the beginning, and it\rquote 
s rather like you being a hitch-hiker. I was seen as somebody transient, and there was one woman in particular, called Jean \endash  I can give you her name now \endash  but she had lost a child that had been run over by a Gorgio, I don\rquote 
t know if I said that to you before? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
