Well, I made some scribbled notes, there were various articles that I later listened to over the years. There was another book called The Official Statistics - I\rquote ve go
t upstairs - showing (that came out the time when I was at Essex) how you could have 80% answer yes, but it\rquote s actually 80% inaccurate. So just because it\rquote s the majority said X, it doesn\rquote t mean it\rquote 
s true. And I remember this wonderful guy \endash  I made notes \endash  he was talking on the radio years ago, and he said, \'93The more you generalise, the more you lose the detail, and in the end you\rquote re left with banalities\'94. And that\rquote 
s what I felt. But, of course, you know, I\rquote m more sympathetic to Barbara now, retrospectively, but she kept saying, \'93This is a policy-oriented (the dreaded word!) policy-oriented project\'94, and \'93The government will only respond to numbers
\'94. She actually said, \'93The ideal for this report\'94 - which is what we thought we were going to produce \endash  was to hav
e tables on every page, of figures. You know, totally bogus! I began to look at that, government Census, and in the Census it talked about real Romanies and reproduced the stuff, and she had a photograph of a gypsy marriage in that Census \endash  I
\rquote ve got it upstairs in my attic \endash  and it said, \'93A gypsy marries for life\'94. She just repeated what a gypsy said, which when you began to unpick it, of course - of course, my wonderful (what would I say? \'93weapon\'94
 is a brilliant article by Edmund Leach, which I hadn\rquote t read at the time \endash  it was published in 1967, and I refer to it in my book. I\rquote 
m sending the final thing tomorrow, by e-mail, by the way. In this book, Anthropological Practice, an utterly brilliant article called, \'93An anthropologist\rquote s reflections on a social survey\'94. I\rquote 
ve actually referred to it here in the Appendix. There it is there. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
