\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 I just listened, yes. Yeah. But that\rquote s where the linguists hate me. I mean, absolutely hate me, because I only listened to w
hat was there, and I thought it was very important, socially, what words they chose to speak in the other language. \'93Gava\'94 for policeman; \'93chavvy\'94 for child; \'93mocatee\'94 for polluted; \'93prasta\'94
 is to run. And then you never say the name of a rat inside a caravan, you just say \'93longtail\'94. All those things were terribly - linguists like Yarron Matras (?? \endash  60.34 - sp) at Manchester, he\rquote s not interested in that. Forgive me if I
\rquote ve said it before, because I gave a speech in France, in Tours, about two weeks ago, at a Roma event \endash 
 little did I know that so many pages into my book, The Traveller Gypsies, I had questioned the reduction of all customs to origin, which again I got straight from Leach and Malinowski. You don\rquote t explain people\rquote s beliefs solely in terms of 
origin. \'93Oh, they do it because 300 years ago they did that\'94, which implied that all non-Western people don\rquote t have a sense of history or change. I said I was interested in why they used \'93chavvy\'94 instead of \'93child\'94
 - of course, you know, the chavs have adopted that now. By the way, the word \'93pal\'94, \'93pal\'94 is actually a Romany word that comes from the East End of London. It\rquote s used in the East End of London, but it\rquote s a Romany word, \'93pal\'94
. Yeah. So I wrote these few pages. I was very friendly, at that point, with
 a good anthropologist who was doing work on miners in the North-East, she was at Brown University, called Jane Zurich, and she encouraged me to discuss Marxism. I was already a Marxist, but I was inspired, and I mentioned Marx in that first chapter where
 
I say that gypsies - is it a coincidence that gypsies appeared throughout Europe with the collapse of feudalism? And therefore there were many landless peasants and serfs, and disbanded armies, thrown into the workplace or whatever, and, therefore, I didn
\rquote t mean all gypsies were ex-serfs, but that language travels independently of people. That\rquote s why this Yarron Matras, the linguists, hate me. It\rquote s also, to be quite frank, because I\rquote 
m not Jewish. Donald Kenrick, he is a linguist, he\rquote s approaching 80 now, he did his degree in linguistics, I think, at SOAS, or maybe he didn\rquote t have a degree, I don\rquote 
t know, and I admire his work in that he was speaking on behalf of asylum seekers and refugees. But he was obsessed about the Indian origin, and that they all migrated from India and then the new generation is this Israeli, Yarron Matras, who\rquote 
s managed to offend everybody, not just me. But I was reduced to tears when I read an article by him, that came out of a conference that I attended, and it was a book edited by Susan Tebutt, at Liverpool, and at the Conference she came up to me and said, 
\'93I just love your work, and it\rquote s wonderful\'94. She was a literary person, and her articles are mainly about gypsies in literature, which is very interesting. But then I was sent this 
book to review, and there was this article by this Israeli, who\rquote s got the job in Manchester, there are some things I don\rquote t know whether to say, but in this book, he said, \'93
Judith Okely is on a self-righteous crusade to destroy gypsy history\'94. And I actually rang up the AUT because I thought that was libellous \endash  that I wanted to destroy gypsy history? And then I rang up Liverpool University - the AUT said they didn
\rquote t take on libel cases, and I rang up the Liverpool University Press, and I said, \'93I\rquote ve worked most of my research life on behalf of gypsies, and you publish this defamatory thing\'94. And they were pretty scared, but I haven\rquote 
t got the money. Then I rang up Susan Tebutt, and said, \'93You told me you admired my work, and you\rquote ve edited a book saying that I\rquote m on a self-righteous crusade to destroy gypsy history\'94, and I was on the ROM-net, \'93
Judith Okely is the enemy of the Roma people\'94. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
