\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 But Hamish, one of the earlier times when I - I already knew Alan, but Hamish organised an event in the School of Scottis
h Studies, where they showed a film \endash  it was \'93The Scottish Traveller Weekend\'94 \endash  and they showed a film of \'93the tent people\'94. And again, there was the same old theme, but then it wasn\rquote t they carry Indian customs, it\rquote 
s that Scottish travellers carry our true
 Pictish Celtic culture. They are leftovers, and they are embodiment of our culture before the wicked English conquered us. So they had these windblown scenes of tents and romantic music, and then they showed them working away at a piece of metal, saying,
 \'93This is the continuing tradition of them as tinkers\'94
. I mean, they were in iron and steel, smashing up cars, but would you say this was proof of Celtic Pictish culture? Oh, it was appalling! And then they had Scottish travellers come in and sing, and I kn
ew that they were highly literate performers on the circuit, but Hamish would [say], \'93This is the embodiment of true Scottish culture\'94
. And the travellers got more and more drunk, and they were singing songs, sort of Country and Western, and one of the travellers \endash  and, of course, there were lots of Americans who were doing a course on Scottish culture, there was a special week
\rquote s event, and they were taking photographs \endash  and at one point, this drunken Scottish traveller said, \'93I don\rquote t know any tinky songs!\'94
 So he spoke for me really! (LAUGHS) But, you know, the scepticism! Nomads are the embodiment frozen in time, and they don\rquote t have any link with history or modern life, and that was what was being repeated in My Gypsy Wedding \endash 
 the voice over saying, \'93The gypsies are finally confronting the 21st century, they\rquote ve been isolated and secret\'94. I thought, \'93I fought that in the 1970s\'94. I mean, it\rquote s voice over crap! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
