ategic in one way, but I had no idea about how to exploit one\rquote s career contacts\'94. I thought, \'93I can\rquote t publish that in an article if I\rquote m going to have it in the book\'94. So I said, \'93Well, it\rquote 
s already going to be in my book\'94. And, of course, if I had publishe
d it, I would have been far more immune from venom if I had Eric Hobsbawm supporting me in Past and Present. It would have given it a certain status. But instead, I mean, like Donald Kenrick, he said, \'93Every time I read your book I want to burn it\'94
. So I said, \'93Oh, so you believe in Nazi book burning, do you?\'94 And that sort of got him! }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
