ve done an article in her honour, where she was the one that ran the all women\rquote s seminar. She came up to me and said, \'93Judith, will you give a paper on gypsy women?\'94 and that was when I thought, as a Feminist, I\rquote d never really t
hought that I should - I thought, well, it was a Feminist act to go to university \endash  that was sufficient \endash  and I\rquote d never extricated the women as a category. I\rquote 
ve written this article in her honour, and then I gave that first version, and then it appeared later in her book, Perceiving Women, which was the first anthropology book on post-seventies Feminism. Even now she\rquote s running seminars called \'93
Ethnicity and Identity\'94, she\rquote s still running Edwin\rquote s seminars, as it were. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid16076572 
