\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Yeah, well, I came back in 1999, and every Thursday there\rquote s been a seminar, and I started going. It\rquote 
s a shaky business, because they depended on Directors who were either with a husband\rquote s salary, it wasn\rquote t the sort of thing that somebody with a full
-time job could take on, and often they were the wives of academics. Oxford was full of women who were highly qualified, but they couldn\rquote 
t get jobs. And the Deputy Director suddenly invited me out for lunch in about 2001, and then they said, the Deputy, she\rquote d just got a tutorial job in an Oxford College, and they said, \'93Would you take over?\'94 And I said, \'93As long as it isn
\rquote t anything to do with admin. because\'94, I said, \'93I left my job because I found admin. was destroying my intellect\'94. And so they said, \'93Well, we need your name, and it\rquote s nice to have a professor\'94
. So I was always on the bottom of the notepaper. Every term we arranged seminars, and I\rquote ve had some quite sensational seminars. I had one with Lydia Sciama. She was a post-grad. when I was a post-gra
d., along with Helen Calloway, but they were older than me, and they were, as usual, the wives of academics, who\rquote d had to follow their husbands, couldn\rquote 
t get jobs, but then they did Ph.D.s once their children were at secondary school. She and I ran a whole seminar on the Mediterranean, and I got students to, I got Heysham (?? \endash  sp -13.46) - unfortunately he couldn\rquote 
t come over, but I read his paper on the Bedouin. And last summer I had a whole seminar on \'93Politics and Giving Back\'94, and that we\rquote re not just researchers who take material. \'93What reciprocity is there?\'94
 I had some big names. I had Johnny Parry, the one who married Margaret who I met at the Sorbonne, and he has been in a continuing problem, because his key research assistant was arrested as a terror
ist about six years ago, on totally bogus charges, and he was giving a paper about how the anthropologist fights to release their own assistant. And Tony Simpson, the one who talked about HIV. I can say this, but it\rquote 
s still in confidence, that LMH have been open to us transferring, but we\rquote re not going to be given a room or Visiting Fellows, it\rquote s just running a seminar. I\rquote ve got a wall of Feminist books upstairs, and I\rquote 
