\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 It\rquote s this David Morgan on that book \endash  the one who was then employed by the 
West Midlands, and asked for our names to be deleted from the chapters, and he died before the eighties. So it\rquote s not that same David Morgan. I met him once. But Wendy James, it\rquote s quite ironic that I\rquote 
ve only been invited once to give a Friday Seminar, and that\rquote s the big event. I gave a Friday Seminar, I came back from Durham in about 1977, and I gave a presentation. In those days, you just had photocopies, you didn\rquote 
t even have an overhead projector, I passed round photocopies of pictures of the gypsies which I got from the local \endash  because that\rquote 
s the wonderful thing is that I went to the local archives of the local papers, and all the photographs, nearly all of them in my book, are actually of the people I knew - but most of the newspapers even agreed not to h
ave the area name of the newspaper, so it didn\rquote t identify them. It\rquote s only one. Anyway, I was showing these pictures as I was elaborating on pollution beliefs and everything else, and Wendy James, it was thanks to her, she said, \'93
That photograph of the graveside, why are there wreaths of chairs?\'94 And I can show you, again, with that book. \'93Why chairs?\'94 It was her perception and it\rquote s like \'93Eureka!\'94
 And that helped me. Part of my chapter on death rituals is reproduced in an Open University book just from last year, on death and bereavement. They\rquote 
ve reproduced my section, because I was the first to write on death rituals in gypsies in Europe. And I suddenly thought, \'93Why?\'94 And then, bingo! It was settlement. It was sedentarisation. The chair \endash  because they didn\rquote 
t have chairs in their caravans, they had benches \endash  and I suddenly thought, \'93It\rquote s settlement. The ghost is settled\'94. And that\rquote s why I thanked Wendy. Just that one perceptive comment. Although, in those days, she said, \'93
Judith, it was so good you showing photographs, because it shows they\rquote re human\'94. It was considered sensational to show pictures of people! So that\rquote s why I thanked Wendy James. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
