\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 The gypsy book. But I finished the conclusion literally, or the proofs, the day befor
e I moved to Essex. It was that close. I was at a loose end. I wasn\rquote t sure what I was going to do, I can\rquote t remember what plans I had, but to celebrate the 50th anniversary of the publication of de Beauvoir\rquote 
s The Second Sex, and the new translation, it was 1974, so it was 30 years since the publication, that\rquote s right. Thirty years since the publication of de Beauvoir\rquote 
s Second Sex. There was a big event in London, and a number of us all offered papers, and that\rquote s when I gave a presentation which did use my own volume \endash  because I\rquote d read it in French, I didn\rquote 
t even know how bad the translation was. I\rquote d read it in 1961 in Paris. And I gave a rough little thing about how ridiculous it was that I had to underline the thing saying, \'93Women\rquote s intelligence is equal to men\'94. [INTERRUPTION] }{
