\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, this is what I\rquote 
m leading to, is that Fabian said that the anthropologist has privileged the visual, as opposed to all the other senses, and there was a rash of material that came out about the ethnographic taste of things, or the senses and the body, and Fabian\rquote 
s examples were always of team research, people going to an area, and then they, as it were, looked. I, again, remembered such a resource, thanks to Agar, a brilliant film called, Les Enfants du Paradis, with Jean-Louis Barrault in it. I don\rquote 
