\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Ann Oakley\rquote s, that\rquote s a classic \endash 
 it really is. And people were very upset. And somebody wrote it up in the Anthropology Today saying that, \'93It\rquote s all very well for Judith Okely, there are people looking for jobs now.\'94 They thought that I was saying you can\rquote 
t teach it, so the poor young man who\rquote d written this commentary, he was terrified (LAUGHS) when I wrote a reply! And I sent him my reading list, eight weeks course on fieldwork! He completely wrote a humble apology. (LAUGHS) But they 
misunderstood. They thought I meant that you must just go into the field without any ideas, and I just said, \'93No, no, no, you just learn that there\rquote 
s so many different possibilities, that you have to be open, but the irony and the brilliance of these interviews is commonalities\'94. It\rquote s just exciting. Some people say, \'93Well, you know, you fix the editing\'94
. No. They all - except Louise, she had to shift a bit and she should have shifted much more - they changed their focus when in the field, and it\rquote s absolutely crucial. So again, it\rquote 
s an attack on preordained research topics. Also the role of chance and accident. I\rquote ve got the first possibility of \endash  this has appeared finally \endash  \'93Ethnographic Practice in the Present\'94 \endash  I mean, they\rquote 
ve nicked my bit, but it\rquote s an article. I have to think what\rquote s the exact title? I took a theme of Freud, and the reason why was this conference was held in Vienna, and I said \endash 
 and actually, the Austrians were delighted. I was the only one that mentioned that we were in Vienna, the place where Freud lived. I said, \'93I went to fieldwork as free association and free passage\'94. I said, in my talk, \'93I went to Freud\rquote 
s Museum yesterday, and to celebrate this city, I\rquote m going to take Freud\rquote s notion of free association \endash  how it is used in the field\'94. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
