Mmm. Mmm. Yeah. And also, mis-hearings. I mean, the classic mis-hearings is that dear Malcolm McLeod, who was a student of Evans-Pritchard, he was his research assistant here. He said how a French anthropologist \endash  and he still won\rquote 
t say who it is \endash  was visiting Oxford, and as usual, they were in the pub, and Evans-Pritchard said, \'93Malcolm McLeod is interested in studying witchcraft in Africa, and can you suggest anything?\'94 I mean, it was years since Evans-Pritchard
\rquote s book on the Azandi (?? \endash  sp. 12.17), absolutely celebrated classic. And this Frenchman said, \'93Oh, the Ashanti\'94, which is in Ghana. So Malcolm, in those days, you had to do a B.Litt.. You didn\rquote t have to do one did you? }{
