\rquote s never \endash  except for that one woman that Jim was involved with, and he only got involved with her because they shared digs \endash  that he can\rquote t actually live with anybody. So I bought the flat next to him, whic
h was amazing, because it was up for sale, so we were in adjoining flats in the High Street. But he\rquote s, in a way, a tragic figure, [who writes] brilliant stuff. I mean, he did work amongst the Wiyampi (?? \endash  39.17 \endash 
 sp) in Brazil, absolutely classic anthropology. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
