\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 Well, Andy Dawson came up and visited me in Edinburgh, and he said, \'93Judith, pack your bags and come to Hull, because there\rquote 
s a professorship going\'94. I said, \'93Look, I\rquote ve just moved to a new place, and I\rquote ve got a new kitchen.\'94. \'93Oh, Judith, you can do it!\'94
 So that was one reason, that it was impossible being in the same Department with somebody one had a close relationship [which was ending]. ... Then the other major thing was being English in Scotland, being with a Scotsman was 
fine, and being up in the Highlands, they weren\rquote 
t anti-English. He had a beautiful little mini cottage up there, and they welcomed me and adored me. But being in Edinburgh, the hatred of English was unspeakable, and it was very very useful to understand racism. And so I had nobody to hide behind. \'93
You fucking bitch. You get back to your fucking country\'94, and \'93You fucking well voted for Thatcher\'94. Of course, after the 1994 Election, I didn\rquote t appear in any shops speaking English accent, because the hatred, because there wasn\rquote 
t a single Conservative MP left in Scotland, but they returned Major. A rather impressive Australian woman, she\rquote s called Ann Fink \endash  she did a Ph.D. in Oxford] and then she moved up to Edinburgh because her husband was a big professor of su
rgery or something at Edinburgh, and I rang her to say, \'93Look am I paranoid to think that I\rquote m leaving Scotland because I can\rquote t stand being labelled as an English bitch?\'94 And she said, \'93You\rquote re absolutely right\'94. She\rquote 
d modified her Australian accent when she\rquote 
d come to Oxford, but you could still pick it up. She was very wealthy, she drove her BMW down a one-way off Princes Street, and it was the wrong way. She put down the window, and there were three Scotsmen there, and she said, \'93I\rquote 
ve done a very silly thing, I\rquote ve gone up a one-way the wrong way. Could you just stand there as I back out?\'94 And they said, \'93That\rquote s typical, you English bitch. You fucking well bitch. You don\rquote t know how to drive\'94
. And she said, \'93I\rquote m not an English bitch, I\rquote m an Australian bitch, but you peasants wouldn\rquote t know the difference\'94. So I said, \'93Ann, you\rquote ve solved my problem!\'94 (LAUGHS) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
