\par Judith:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 He was in an iron lung, paralysed from the neck down, and he said, \'93Could my daughters wave at me the other side of a glass?\'94
 And, again, my mother, we were at the boarding school, she claimed that the Headmistress said no. So that\rquote s another reason for hating the Headmistress. I mean, he was about 34. I\rquote 
m tormented by the way they handled death. They just said he had \lquote flu, and all I could think of was that \'93Daddy borrowed three shillings from my pig money box and he hasn\rquote t paid me back\'94. And then when you discover he\rquote 
s died, the guilt! I used to think - I don\rquote t know if you know that wonderful detective series called Monk? A brilliant series. He\rquote s an obsessive - I bought the whole series on DVD \endash 
 and he is obsessive, when he walks he has to touch each lamp post, but he\rquote s a brilliant person because he can spot things like Sherlock Holmes. He\rquote s brought in as a consultant. I used to think it was because I picked May \endash  it\rquote 
s supposed to be unlucky to pick May when it\rquote s in blossom \endash  and I thought, \'93I picked May when I was in Lincolnshire, and that\rquote s why he died\'94. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\f39\fs22\lang2057\langfe2057\langnp2057\insrsid4982948\charrsid4982948 
